<ApexClass xmlns="http://soap.sforce.com/2006/04/metadata">
    <apiVersion>48.0</apiVersion>
    <status>Active</status>
    <description>Apex class to handle editing of Student records such as student name, student ID, student grade.</description>
    <userStory>As a user, I want to be able to edit Student records such as student name, student ID, student grade. using a Lightning Web Component and Apex class so that I can improve the user experience for my organization's Salesforce users.</userStory>
    <acceptanceCriteria>The Lightning Web Component should use a lightning-record-edit-form to display the Student record fields such as student name, student ID, student grade. The Apex class should handle the record updates and perform any necessary validation. The user should be able to edit all fields on the Student record such as student name, student ID, student grade. Any validation errors should be displayed to the user in a clear and user-friendly manner. The Lightning Web Component and Apex class should adhere to Salesforce best practices and coding standards.</acceptanceCriteria>
    <definitionOfDone>The Lightning Web Component and Apex class should be developed and tested in a Salesforce sandbox or scratch org. The code should be thoroughly reviewed by at least one other developer. Automated tests should be written to ensure that the code works as expected and any potential issues are caught early. The code should be deployed to a production environment using a Salesforce change set or another deployment tool. The code should be documented, including any assumptions or constraints. The system administrator should be trained on how to use and maintain the new functionality.</definitionOfDone>
</ApexClass>